===Etymology===
From {{der|en|enm|Messyas}}, {{m|enm|Messy}}, {{m|enm|Messie}}, from {{der|en|la|Messias}}, from Hellenistic {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|Μεσσίας}}, from {{etyl|arc|en}} {{m|arc|משיחא|tr=məšīḥā}}, from {{etyl|hbo|en}} {{m|he|מָשִׁיחַ||anointed|tr=māšîaḥ}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|mə-sī'ə}}, {{IPA|/məˈsaɪ.ə/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|Abrahamic tradition}} The one who is ordained by [[God]] to lead the people of [[Israel]], believed by Christians to be [[Jesus Christ]].
# An extremely powerful divine figure.

